	  <concept id="i1099698"
            ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3"
            class="- topic/topic concept/concept ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">19.1309</ph> Contract clauses.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <ol id="d1238e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1252e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause <xref href="FAR-i1057314.dita#i1057314"
                        base="i1057314"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-3</xref>, Notice of HUBZone Set-Aside or Sole Source Award, in solicitations and contracts for acquisitions that are set aside, or reserved for, or awarded on a sole source basis to, HUBZone small business concerns under <xref href="FAR-i1099604.dita#i1099604"
                        base="i1099604"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1305</xref> or <xref href="FAR-i1099639.dita#i1099639"
                        base="i1099639"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">19.1306</xref>. This includes multiple-award contracts when orders may be set aside for HUBZone small business concerns as described in <xref href="FAR-i1117805.dita#i1117805"
                        base="i1117805"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">8.405-5</xref> and <xref href="FAR-i1104008.dita#i1104008"
                        base="i1104008"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">16.505</xref>(b)(2)(i)(F).</p>
					          <ol id="d1238e39" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1252e43" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The contracting officer shall use the clause with its Alternate I to waive the 50 percent requirement if the conditions at <xref href="FAR-i1099682.dita#i1099682"
                              base="i1099682"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1308</xref>(b) apply.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1252e55" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                If a waiver is granted, the HUBZone small business prime contractor must still meet the performance of work requirements set forth in 13 CFR 125.6(c).</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1252e66" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            The contracting officer shall insert the clause at FAR <xref href="FAR-i1057352.dita#i1057352"
                        base="i1057352"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">52.219-4</xref>, Notice of Price Evaluation Preference for HUBZone Small Business Concerns, in solicitations and contracts for acquisitions conducted using full and open competition.</p>
					          <ol id="d1238e75" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1252e79" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The contracting officer shall use the clause with its Alternate I to waive the 50 percent requirement if the conditions at <xref href="FAR-i1099682.dita#i1099682"
                              base="i1099682"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">19.1308</xref>(b) apply.</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1252e91" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                If a waiver is granted, the HUBZone small business prime contractor must still meet the performance of work requirements set forth in 13 CFR 125.6(c).</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
